item.description:
Note the new room and different format for this meeting. The normal meeting room is booked solid in September.

For September 24th we are limited to the smaller Conference Room on the second level. There is a hard limit on the seating in this room, it's literally a conference table with chairs.

I know there are more than a few of you working on some interesting things, so...

I'm hoping to have up to 12 folks who are willing to discuss, for 5-10 minutes each, the projects they are working on, interested in, or need help with. This will be low key, the projector is available but not required for such a small group. It will be a great way to get early feedback from other developers.

There may be room for some "observers" at this discussion, but I prefer to have mostly active participants for this one meeting.
item.how_to_find_us: Conference Room on the upper level
item.name: iPhone Developer Roundtable 9/24 7-9 PM
